-- Related Names Blau CEO and Ross to Continue as Chairman
-- B y   O s h r a t   C a r m i e l
-- 2012-09-07T18:29:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-07/related-names-blau-ceo-and-ross-to-continue-as-chairman.html
Related Cos., developer of
 Manhattan ’s Time Warner Center, named Jeff Blau its chief
executive officer, replacing founder Stephen Ross, who will
remain executive chairman.  Blau, 44, has worked at New York-based Related for 22 years
and has been president since 2000. Bruce Beal Jr., 42,
previously executive vice president, will become president, the
company said in a statement today. The changes are effective
immediately, said  Joanna Rose , Related’s spokeswoman.  “Jeff and Bruce have been my partners for over a decade,”
Ross, 72, said in the statement. “They are exceptional
businessmen and great leaders with extraordinary abilities.”  As executive chairman, Ross is responsible for global
business strategy and overseeing development of the 26-acre (10-
hectare) Hudson Yards project on Manhattan’s far west side,
according to the statement.  Related has a multimillion-dollar pipeline of projects
under development in such cities as Chicago, Boston,  Abu Dhabi 
and Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
